White people and non-black people's guide to the work of Simone Leigh, screts , anti-colonial space making. Holding space, an act of touching and proximity, a gesture of hinding rather than division. - refusing to make room for whiteness. (Park) Her action reimagined space; she was reshaping rather than territorializing. .. predicament of whiteness is its constant demand that everyone "else" legimiate themselves in the face of it. the figures are not giving up secrets